main event: A bright light was seen approaching from the West and passed East at a fast rate of speed in Winslow, Arizona on February 5, 1958.
interesting points: The light appeared larger than a bright star., The sighting lasted for 10-15 seconds., The object made no sound during the observation., The source of the report was considered reliable., No additional information was available to identify the sighting.
witness description: Public sources, no specific witness details provided.
